title: Solana [SOL] outshines Ethereum [ETH] on this crucial parameter - AMBCrypto News
summary: Solana (SOL) has outperformed Ethereum (ETH) in terms of decentralization, according to a recent report. The Nakamoto Coefficient, which measures the decentralization of a blockchain, stood at 31 for Solana compared to 1 for Ethereum. Solana's distribution of validator nodes is also more evenly distributed across geographies, with no country controlling 33% of the active stake. Additionally, Solana has two validator clients to help in case of emergencies, and the network has experienced several network glitches in the past. Despite these issues, Solana's market cap in BTC terms has remained positive, fueled by improving market conditions and increasing development activity.

title: Microsoft Tests Ethereum Wallet Integration In Edge Web Browser - Blockzeit
summary: Microsoft is testing a crypto wallet on its Edge browser, allowing users to store and hold Ethereum tokens and other cryptocurrencies. The wallet is non-custodial, giving users full control of their funds. Microsoft has been actively involved in supporting Web3-related projects and has introduced metaverse features in its Teams app. While the company has not confirmed the existence of the crypto wallet, the testing marks a significant step towards mainstream adoption of cryptocurrencies.
